The “fulcrum flexibility”, a measure of the spinal flexibility as revealed by the fulcrum-bending radiograph [11, 17] was calculated based on the following formula: \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}
$$ \begin{aligned}{} & {\text{Fulcrum flexibility (\% ) = }}\frac{{{\text{Preop cobb angle - FB cobb angle}}}} {{{\text{Preop cobb angle}}}}{\text{ $ \times $ 100}} \\ & \\ \end{aligned} $$\end{document} where FB stands for fulcrum bending.
